{
  "text": "As shown in the fine mapping analysis of GWAS, the rs1058319 T N C variant in the 3'UTR of SLC2A4RG was associated with increased glioma risk [CITATION_1] . Since 3'-UTR plays a pivotal role in modulating stability and translation of mRNA [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , our experiment confirmed that the risk C allele decreased the expression of SLC2A4RG compared with wildtype T (Supplementary Fig. S9 ). The risk allele of rs1058319 may change the structural fold of SLC2A4RG mRNA that affects its stability or leads to the impaired polyadenylation process, which may explain why SLC2A4RG is down-regulated in glioma and needs further investigation [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] . Moreover, the possible etiology of glioma associated with SLC2A4RG is also presented by another result that the G N T transversion at rs8957 (E[GAG]233D[GAU]) might impair the nuclear export signal or protein folding of SLC2A4RG, resulting in excess accumulation of unphysiological protein in the nucleus [CITATION_8] .",
  "correct_citation": {
